        <mxCell id="umg2lsHJZ5c2LKmZp1gF-40" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" value="Bridging Management: How should we handle asset and state synchronization between L1 and L2? Will Mantra provide a native bridge, or should we consider third-party solutions?&#xa;&#xa;=&gt; It should be discussed with Mantra Team. As per our assumption, the private asset data stays off-chain and can be accessed through Inveniam Secure APIs. So, it needs to be discussed with Mantra Team. After that, further planning will be effective. &#xa;&#xa;In case of transactions syncronization, Mantra L1 uses hyperlane to facilitate fast cross-chain transactions across the largest L1 networks via Hyperlane.&#xa;https://docs.mantrachain.io/introduction/why-build-on-mantra-chain" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="560" x="-1420" y="170" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="umg2lsHJZ5c2LKmZp1gF-41" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" value="Integration Path: If the L2 is EVM-compatible, integration can likely reuse our existing pipelines. If it’s based on CosmWasm, we’ll need to assess the impact — new infrastructure for contract deployment, transactions, and possibly new SDKs or APIs.&#xa;&#xa;=&gt; L2 is multi-vm chain and it is compatible with CosmWasmVM and EVM. So, we can choose any of the path. &#xa;Note: IBC between CosmWasm and EVM should be established for L2.&#xa;=&gt; As L2 will interacting with AI-Agents and private asset data, we need to ensure the block confrimity has been done.&#xa;=&gt; https://mantra.gitbook.io/inveniam" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="560" x="-1420" y="-10" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="umg2lsHJZ5c2LKmZp1gF-42" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" value="Performance &amp; Scalability: What performance or fee advantages should we expect from L2?&#xa;=&gt; TBD&#xa;=&gt; Will there be any contracts or channels to interact with Inveniam Off-Chain Eco-System ?&#xa;            - If exisits, then is one-directional or bi-directional ?&#xa;            - If bi-directional, can we send write requests ? and what will be fees applicable ?&#xa;&#xa;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="560" x="-1419" y="531" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="umg2lsHJZ5c2LKmZp1gF-43" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" value="Tooling &amp; Dev Environment: What SDKs, APIs, or dev tools are available for CosmWasm (if required)?&#xa;=&gt; Yes, Dev tools and SDKs are available.&#xa;=&gt; But, it is better to develop few new contracts to facilicate a better and future-ready interactions." vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="170" width="560" x="-1420" y="350" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="umg2lsHJZ5c2LKmZp1gF-44" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;fillColor=#ffe6cc;strokeColor=#d79b00;" value="Risk &amp; Readiness: What is the maturity level of L2 environments on Mantra? What would be the minimal integration test plan to validate core interactions (deployment, transaction, read/write)?&#xa;=&gt; TBD. But following points need to be discussed with Mantra team&#xa;&#xa;1. How the interaction with AI-Agents and Private Asset Data will be utilized in Mantra L2 Chain ?&#xa;2. How the validators will validate a block with needs off-chain interaction with Inveniam&#xa;3. What is the definition of AI-Agents&#xa;- Is it refering the Invenam AI Agents and their MCPs ?&#xa;- Or, will L2 have another AI-Agent MCP which can be used to make transaction in L2 ?" vertex="1">
